# JWT Authentication Implementation Plan

## Context

The Express/TypeScript API currently has no authentication. All routes are public, and `userId` is hardcoded to `1` when creating posts/comments. The goal is to add JWT-based auth so that:
- Users can register and log in to receive a JWT token
- Write operations (POST/PUT/DELETE) on posts and comments require a valid token (401 otherwise)
- Ownership is enforced on PUT/DELETE — only the resource owner may modify/delete it (403 otherwise)
- GET endpoints remain public
- JWT secret is `"super-secret-key"`

The test suite in `tests/auth.test.ts` already defines the complete expected behavior. All existing tests in `tests/posts.test.ts` and `tests/comments.test.ts` must continue to pass (they only test public GET endpoints).

**Key facts from codebase:**
- `jsonwebtoken` and `@types/jsonwebtoken` are already installed
- TypeScript with `"module": "Node16"` — all imports use `.js` extensions
- In-memory data store (`src/db.ts`) with seed users (alice/bob/charlie, plaintext passwords)
- `"strict": true` in tsconfig — need proper typing for `req.user`
- Vitest runs tests directly (no tsc step needed for tests)

---

## Files to Create

### 1. `src/middleware/auth.ts` — JWT authenticate middleware

```typescript
import { Request, Response, NextFunction } from "express";
import jwt from "jsonwebtoken";

export const JWT_SECRET = "super-secret-key";

export function authenticate(req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction): void {
  const authHeader = req.headers.authorization;
  if (!authHeader || !authHeader.startsWith("Bearer ")) {
    res.status(401).json({ error: "No token provided" });
    return;
  }
  const token = authHeader.split(" ")[1];
  try {
    const decoded = jwt.verify(token, JWT_SECRET) as { id: number; username: string };
    req.user = decoded;
    next();
  } catch {
    res.status(401).json({ error: "Invalid token" });
  }
}
```

### 2. `src/routes/auth.ts` — Register and login routes

```typescript
import { Router } from "express";
import jwt from "jsonwebtoken";
import { users, nextId } from "../db.js";
import { JWT_SECRET } from "../middleware/auth.js";

const router = Router();

// POST /auth/register
router.post("/register", (req, res) => {
  const { username, email, password } = req.body;
  if (!username || !email || !password) {
    res.status(400).json({ error: "username, email, and password are required" });
    return;
  }
  if (users.find((u) => u.username === username)) {
    res.status(409).json({ error: "Username already taken" });
    return;
  }
  const newUser = { id: nextId(users), username, email, password };
  users.push(newUser);
  const token = jwt.sign({ id: newUser.id, username: newUser.username }, JWT_SECRET);
  res.status(201).json({
    token,
    user: { id: newUser.id, username: newUser.username, email: newUser.email },
  });
});

// POST /auth/login
router.post("/login", (req, res) => {
  const { username, password } = req.body;
  const user = users.find((u) => u.username === username);
  if (!user || user.password !== password) {
    res.status(401).json({ error: "Invalid credentials" });
    return;
  }
  const token = jwt.sign({ id: user.id, username: user.username }, JWT_SECRET);
  res.json({ token });
});

export { router as authRouter };
```

---

## Files to Modify

### 3. `src/types.ts` — Augment Express Request with `user` property

Append a `declare global` block to give `req.user` a type throughout the app (required by `"strict": true`):

```typescript
// ... existing interfaces unchanged ...

declare global {
  namespace Express {
    interface Request {
      user?: { id: number; username: string };
    }
  }
}
```

### 4. `src/app.ts` — Register the auth router

Add the import and mount it at `/auth` before other routes:

```typescript
import { authRouter } from "./routes/auth.js";
// ...
app.use("/auth", authRouter);
app.use("/posts", postsRouter);
app.use(commentsRouter);
```

### 5. `src/routes/posts.ts` — Protect write routes + ownership checks

Changes:
- Import `authenticate` from `"../middleware/auth.js"`
- `POST /`: add `authenticate` middleware; use `req.user!.id` instead of `userId || 1`
- `PUT /:id`: add `authenticate`; after finding post, check `post.userId !== req.user!.id` → 403
- `DELETE /:id`: add `authenticate`; after finding post, check `post.userId !== req.user!.id` → 403
- GET routes: unchanged (stay public)

Example for POST:
```typescript
router.post("/", authenticate, (req, res) => {
  const { title, content } = req.body;
  if (!title || !content) { ... }
  const newPost: Post = {
    id: nextId(posts), title, content,
    userId: req.user!.id,          // ← from token, not body
    createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),
  };
  posts.push(newPost);
  res.status(201).json(newPost);
});
```

Example ownership check for PUT/DELETE:
```typescript
router.put("/:id", authenticate, (req, res) => {
  // ... find post, 404 if missing ...
  if (posts[index].userId !== req.user!.id) {
    res.status(403).json({ error: "Forbidden" });
    return;
  }
  // ... update ...
});
```

### 6. `src/routes/comments.ts` — Protect write routes + ownership checks

Changes:
- Import `authenticate` from `"../middleware/auth.js"`
- `POST /posts/:postId/comments`: add `authenticate`; use `req.user!.id` instead of `userId || 1`
- `PUT /comments/:id`: add `authenticate`; ownership check (403 for non-owner)
- `DELETE /comments/:id`: add `authenticate`; ownership check (403 for non-owner)
- GET routes: unchanged (stay public)

---

## Summary of Route Protection Matrix

| Method | Route                         | Auth Required | Ownership Check |
|--------|-------------------------------|---------------|-----------------|
| GET    | /posts                        | No            | No              |
| GET    | /posts/:id                    | No            | No              |
| POST   | /posts                        | Yes (401)     | No              |
| PUT    | /posts/:id                    | Yes (401)     | Yes (403)       |
| DELETE | /posts/:id                    | Yes (401)     | Yes (403)       |
| GET    | /posts/:postId/comments       | No            | No              |
| GET    | /comments/:id                 | No            | No              |
| POST   | /posts/:postId/comments       | Yes (401)     | No              |
| PUT    | /comments/:id                 | Yes (401)     | Yes (403)       |
| DELETE | /comments/:id                 | Yes (401)     | Yes (403)       |

---

## Verification

Run the full test suite:
```bash
npm test
```

Expected: all tests in `auth.test.ts`, `posts.test.ts`, and `comments.test.ts` pass.

Key scenarios to verify manually if needed:
1. `POST /auth/register` → 201 with `{ token, user }` (no `password` field)
2. `POST /auth/login` with valid credentials → 200 with `{ token }`
3. `POST /auth/login` with wrong password → 401
4. `POST /posts` without `Authorization` header → 401
5. `POST /posts` with `Bearer <token>` → 201, `userId` matches token (not request body)
6. `PUT /posts/:id` as non-owner → 403
7. `DELETE /posts/:id` as owner → 200
8. `GET /posts` (no token) → 200 (still public)

